In a heavy saucepan, combine first seven ingredients. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Cool. Place in a mixing bowl. Dissolve baking soda in hot water; add to mixing bowl. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to batter. Pour into a greased 9-in. x 5-in. x 3-in. loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for about 45 minutes or until cake tests done. Serve with Hard Sauce (also found in Recipe Finder) if desired.